How can I add another storybook theme to this file? 
# Adding Another Storybook Theme

To add another Storybook theme to your configuration, you need to modify your `.storybook/main.ts` file by adding the theme configuration in the `framework.options` section. Here's how to do it:

```ts
import type { StorybookConfig } from "@storybook/experimental-nextjs-vite";

const config: StorybookConfig = {
  "stories": [
    "../src/**/*.mdx",
    "../src/**/*.stories.@(js|jsx|mjs|ts|tsx)"
  ],
  "addons": [{
    "name": "@storybook/addon-essentials",
    "options": {
      "docs": false
    }
  }, "@storybook/addon-onboarding", "@chromatic-com/storybook", "@storybook/experimental-addon-test"],
  "framework": {
    "name": "@storybook/experimental-nextjs-vite",
    "options": {
      "theme": {
        // Your theme options here
        // For example:
        "base": "light", // or "dark"
        "brandTitle": "My Custom Storybook",
        "brandUrl": "https://example.com",
        "brandImage": "/path-to-logo.png",
        // Add more theme properties as needed
      }
    }
  },
  "staticDirs": [
    "../public"
  ]
};
export default config;
```

Alternatively, for more advanced theming, you might want to:

1. Create a `.storybook/preview.ts` file (if you don't have one already)
2. Import and set up your theme there:

```ts
// .storybook/preview.ts
import { themes } from '@storybook/theming';

export default {
  parameters: {
    // Choose one of the built-in themes:
    // themes.light or themes.dark
    // Or import your custom theme
    docs: {
      theme: themes.dark, // or your custom theme
    },
    // You can also set the theme globally:
    theme: themes.dark, // or your custom theme
  },
};
```

For custom themes, you'll need to create a theme file and import it:

```ts
// .storybook/YourCustomTheme.ts
import { create } from '@storybook/theming/create';

export default create({
  base: 'light', // or 'dark'
  brandTitle: 'My Custom Storybook',
  brandUrl: 'https://example.com',
  brandImage: '/path-to-logo.png',
  // Add more theme properties as needed
});

// Then in preview.ts:
import customTheme from './YourCustomTheme';

export default {
  parameters: {
    docs: {
      theme: customTheme,
    },
  },
};
```

This gives you more control over the theming of your Storybook instance.
